%^CYAN%^STATUS EFFECTS%^RESET%^

%^CYAN%^%^ULINE%^Confused%^RESET%^
Confused creatures experience various effects based on a d100 roll:
 %^ORANGE%^ 1...11%^RESET%^ It attacks the confuser
 %^ORANGE%^12...21%^RESET%^ Nothing happens
 %^ORANGE%^22...51%^RESET%^ It stares aimlessly into nothingness
 %^ORANGE%^52...71%^RESET%^ It falls asleep
 %^ORANGE%^72..100%^RESET%^ It attacks random living things present in the same room

%^CYAN%^%^ULINE%^Fast healing%^RESET%^
A creature with the fast healing special quality regains hit points at an exceptional rate. This gives grade*level/3 points of passive regeneration each round. For example, fast healing 2 gives 6 hp regeneration to a level 10 monster per round.

%^CYAN%^%^ULINE%^Fear%^RESET%^
Fear has various effects, depending on what caused it. Sometimes it causes a creature to freeze in fear, or to run away. Sometimes it causes a creature to lose the will to fight.

%^CYAN%^%^ULINE%^Invisible%^RESET%^
Invisible creatures can not be seen by other creatures unless they have the true sight or other ways to detect invisibility. Glitterdust and similar effects will reveal invisible creatures too. Invisible creatures are marked with %^CYAN%^(inv)%^RESET%^ before their name, that is, if you are able to see them.

%^CYAN%^%^ULINE%^Hidden%^RESET%^
Hidden creatures can not be seen by others, as they are hiding in shadows. The room must have less than 3 light levels for anyone to be able to hide in it. You can <search> the room for hidden creatures or use glitterdust to reveal them. <search> reveals the hidden creatures only for you. Hidden creatures are marked with %^ORANGE%^(hid)%^RESET%^ before their name when revealed.

%^CYAN%^%^ULINE%^Paralysis%^RESET%^
A paralyzed creature cannot act. Paralyzed players can not enter many commands.

%^CYAN%^%^ULINE%^Prone or staggered%^RESET%^
Prone or staggered creatures can not use most weapons for the duration of the effect.

%^CYAN%^%^ULINE%^Regeneration%^RESET%^
A creature gets 2d4 regeneration per round as part of its innate ability to heal.

%^CYAN%^%^ULINE%^Temporary blinded%^RESET%^
Blinded creatures can not see or target other creatures unless it can navigate by other means, like sound or smell.
